Linked lists are useful to implement stacks and queues in situations where their size
is subject to vary. Each node in the linked list can be pushed or popped without disturbing
the majority of the nodes. Same goes for insertion/deletion of nodes somewhere in the middle.

More details about LinkedList is here: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linked_list

+--------------------------------------------------------------------------+
|                                                                          |
|                             TIME COMPLEXITY                              |
|                                                                          |
+--------------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
|                                      |                                   |
|             AVERAGE CASE             |            WORST CASE             |
|                                      |                                   |
+--------------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| Access: O(n)                         | O(n)                              |
+--------------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| Search: O(n)                         | O(n)                              |
+--------------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| Insertion: O(1)                      | O(1)                              |
+--------------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| Deletion: O(1)                       | O(1)                              |
+--------------------------------------+-----------------------------------+